Title: Analytical construction of a nonperturbative vacuum for the open bosonic
  string
Authors: Alan Kostelecky and Robertus Potting
Comments: 15 pages, minor corrections and clarifications, accepted in Physical
  Review D
Report-no: IUHET 426, August 2000
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D63 (2001) 046007
\\
  Using analytical methods, a nonpertubative vacuum is constructed recursively
in the field theory for the open bosonic string. Evidence suggests it
corresponds to the Lorentz-invariant endpoint of tachyon condensation on a
D25-brane. The corresponding string field is a twisted squeezed state.
